# DEMA Architecture Rule

## Frontend stack

- Frontend must remain React + TypeScript + Vite.
- Keep feature logic behind repository/store boundaries rather than direct endpoint calls from random components.
- Preserve existing UI flow unless a phase explicitly authorizes redesign.

## Backend stack

- Backend runtime is Python-only.
- FastAPI is the HTTP layer; business logic belongs in services/repositories.
- No parallel non-Python backend runtime is allowed in this project.

## Database target

- PostgreSQL is the production target database.
- SQLite may be used for local/dev smoke checks.
- Database migrations must be managed with Alembic.

## Repository and data-layer rule

- API handlers call services, services call repositories, repositories own persistence details.
- Keep storage provider details (local filesystem, Azure Blob) behind service abstractions.
- Do not leak infrastructure keys or storage credentials to the frontend.

## Docs, tests, and build discipline

- Every phase updates architecture/API/operations docs when behavior changes.
- Backend changes include at least smoke-level tests for affected endpoints.
- Frontend changes must keep `npm run build` green.
- Backend changes must keep migration checks (`alembic current/heads/upgrade`) valid.

## No giant god files

- Avoid adding new giant multi-thousand-line files.
- Split new logic into focused modules by concern (api, services, repositories, schemas, models, docs).
- When touching legacy large files, prefer minimal phase-scoped edits and extract new logic into dedicated modules.
